<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-12-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="264" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                            <head><persName type="from">Mr. Washburn</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Gunnison</persName>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Portland,</hi></placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-12-12"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 12, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Deposition of Charles Johnson, mate of the Chesapeake, taken by
                                United States commissioner, proves conclusively the murder of Orin
                                Shaffer, second engineer, on the morning of December 7, by the
                                pirates who took possession of the steamer. I send the depositions
                                by mail.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>I. WASHBURN, <hi rend="smallcaps">Jr.,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Collector.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>